(1) Slow CKD progression: - RAS inhibitor (ACEi/ARB): max tolerated; target BP < 130/80 (CKD); reduce albuminuria. - SGLT2 inhibitor (dapagliflozin, empagliflozin): DAPA-CKD, EMPA-KIDNEY trials show 30% RRR CKD progression + CV events; benefit in DM + non-DM; safe down to eGFR 20-25. Mainstay now. - Finerenone (non-steroidal MRA): FIDELIO/FIGARO — DKD with albuminuria, K monitoring. - GLP-1 RA (semaglutide): FLOW trial 2024 — renoprotection in DKD. - Glycemic: A1c individualized (7-8% advanced CKD; CGM, avoid hypoglycemia). - BP: < 130/80 (SPRINT individualized in elderly/CKD; KDIGO < 120 SBP individualized). - Lifestyle: weight, exercise, smoking cessation, sodium < 2 g/d, protein 0.8 g/kg/d (avoid < 0.6, malnutrition).

