(4) Pain control;

(5) Avoid air travel until resolved + 1 wk after; lifelong avoid scuba diving (BTS);

(6) Smoking cessation counseling — reduces recurrence 6x;

(7) Recurrence: ~20-50% first-side risk → ipsilateral risk ↑ after first event; pleurodesis (chemical talc, mechanical abrasion) or VATS bullectomy + pleurectomy considered after second ipsilateral or first contralateral or persistent air leak > 5-7 d or high-risk profession (pilot, diver);

