(6) Iatrogenic (post-CVC, thoracentesis): aspiration or tube.

(7) Post-PTX management: - O2 supplementation accelerates resorption. - Avoid air travel until resolved + 1-2 wk. - Avoid SCUBA diving — lifelong if recurrent (relative even with single). - Smoking cessation — recurrence ↓. - Counsel re recognizing recurrence.

(8) Heimlich valve for outpatient management in selected stable PSP — institution-dependent.

(9) Recurrence: PSP 20-50% on same side after first; SSP higher; pleurodesis/surgery after 2nd ipsilateral. A ผิด — large symptomatic = intervention. C ผิด — surgery for recurrent/persistent. D ผิด — alternative not first-line. E ผิด — distractor.

