(1) Diagnosis: PB or BM ≥ 20% blasts; flow + cytogenetics + molecular essential.

(2) Risk stratification (ELN 2022): - Favorable: t(8;21), inv(16)/t(16;16) (CBF AML), NPM1 mutated without FLT3-ITD or with FLT3-ITD low ratio, biallelic CEBPA. - Intermediate: NPM1 + FLT3-ITD high ratio, no adverse, no favorable. - Adverse: complex karyotype, monosomy 5/7, MECOM, TP53, RUNX1, ASXL1, FLT3-ITD without NPM1, others.

